ong>Safety</strong>. When your wheels aren’t aligned, it can cause your vehicle to pull right or left, undermining your control and handling.&nbsp;</p><p>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Comfort</strong>. Aligned wheels improve driving safety but they also make driving easier and more comfortable because you don’t experience steering pulls or wheel shimmying.&nbsp;</p><h2>Can you have preventative alignments performed?&nbsp;</h2><p>Between potholes, gravel roads and everyday winter driving, regular alignments can go a long way toward taking care of the critical systems and components of your vehicle as well as your tires and wheels—helping you save big on major repairs with preventative maintenance.&nbsp;</p><p>We recommend checking your owner’s manual to learn how often the manufacturer recommends alignments, and also checking to see if an alignment is needed during your <a href=\"https://www.kaltire.com/en/winter-tire-changes/\" target=\"_self\" data-link-type=\"external\" data-link-label=\"https://www.kaltire.com/en/winter-tire-changes/\">winter tire changes</a> or every fall/spring if you run one set of <a href=\"https://www.kaltire.com/en/all-weather-tires/\" target=\"_self\" data-link-type=\"external\" data-link-label=\"https://www.kaltire.com/en/all-weather-tires/\">all-weather</a> tires year round.&nbsp;</p>",
