bably adequate. If you can see the tip of the nose, it’s time to bring your vehicle in.</p><h4>With tire tread wear indicators</h4><p>Your tires may also have built-in tread wear indicators. They’re little raised bars—usually six on each tire—along your tires grooves that mark the minimum permitted tread depth. If these indicators are worn, replace your tires right away.</p><h2>Why you want summer tires with a good tread depth</h2><p>Tires at or above the recommended tread depth level can give you better traction, reduced risk of punctures and the ability to dispel moisture so you won’t hydroplane on wet roads.</p><h2>When summer tires reach the end of their life</h2><p>If it’s time for your tires to retire, bring them to any <a href=\"https://www.kaltire.com/en/locations/\" target=\"_self\" data-link-type=\"external\" data-link-label=\"https://www.kaltire.com/en/locations/\">Kal Tire store</a> and we’ll take care of recycling tires for you. You are welcome to drop off up to four off-rim tires so they can be <a href=\"https://www.kaltire.com/en/recycling/\" target=\"_self\" data-link-type=\"external\" data-link-label=\"https://www.kaltire.com/en/recycling/\">recycled</a> into products such as rubber mats and playground surfaces.</p>",
