=\"wiper blades scraping\"></p><h3>Squeaking</h3><p>When the rubber squeaks against the glass in the way only worn wiper blades can, it’s a sure sign they need to be taken off.</p><p><img src=\"/resourcecentre/wiper-blades-squeaking.jpg?$staticlink$\" alt=\"wiper blades squeaking\"></p><p>As soon as you see any kind of change in your driving visibility, it means your wiper blades aren’t contacting the windshield surface properly, and you need to have your wiper blades replaced.</p><p>So many of your driving decisions are based on what you can see. For about $20 and a few minutes of your time, you can help prevent a collision with effective wiper blades.</p>",
